messages.content: What is the purpose of the comfyUI-siliconflow-api-2lab custom node?
The purpose of the comfyUI-siliconflow-api-2lab custom node is to provide an unofficial implementation of the siliconflow API for ComfyUI.
Where can users apply for an API key to use with the siliconflow API?
Users can apply for an API key to use with the siliconflow API at https://cloud.siliconflow.cn/.
After obtaining an API key, where should users add it in order to use the siliconflow API in ComfyUI?
After obtaining an API key, users should add it in the config.json file to use the siliconflow API in ComfyUI.
Where can users find examples of how to use the siliconflow API in ComfyUI?
Users can find examples of how to use the siliconflow API in ComfyUI in the workflow folder.
Is the comfyUI-siliconflow-api-2lab custom node an official implementation of the siliconflow API?
No, the comfyUI-siliconflow-api-2lab custom node is an unofficial implementation of the siliconflow API for ComfyUI.
What is the website URL for applying for a siliconflow API key?
The website URL for applying for a siliconflow API key is https://cloud.siliconflow.cn/.
Which file should users modify to include their siliconflow API key for use with ComfyUI?
Users should modify the config.json file to include their siliconflow API key for use with ComfyUI.
